      <h2 class="huge"><a id="Overview">Overview</a></h2>
      <div class="content">
        <p><em>PhD received in Summer 2011</em>

        <p>Disertation: <a href="http://gradworks.umi.com/34/73/3473568.html">Efficient
          Processing of Set-Similarity Joins on Large
          Clusters</a><br>Advisers: <a href="/~mjcarey">Prof. Michael
          J. Carey</a> and <a href="/~chenli">Prof. Chen Li</a>
          
        <p>
          My research area is large-scale data management and
          data-intensive computing. Since September 2011 I am a
          Research Scientist at HP Labs in Palo Alto, CA.
          
          <!-- In particular, I focus on -->
          <!-- efficient indexing and query processing when the data and -->
          <!-- the query conditions do not match exactly. My advisers -->
          <!-- are <a href="/~mjcarey">Prof. Michael J. Carey</a> -->
          <!-- and <a href="/~chenli">Prof. Chen Li.</a> I am part of -->
          <!-- the <a href="http://isg.ics.uci.edu">Information Systems -->
          <!-- Group</a> at UC Irvine. Recently, I was an intern in -->
          <!-- the <a href="http://www.almaden.ibm.com/cs/disciplines/dm/">Information -->
          <!-- Management</a> group at IBM Almaden Research Center. -->
          
        <p><em>
          
        <!-- <p><em>I am currently looking for a researcher position in the -->
        <!--     area of large-scale data management and data-intensive -->
        <!--     computing.</em> -->
          
        <p>
